<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-108-268 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 980 616</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  July 8 1991 n649 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>LCD researchers are getting active; seminar in Japan coversactive-matrix challenges. (Semiconductor Equipment and MaterialsInternational trade group seminar discusses active-matrixliquid-crystal displays)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kaplan, Douglas.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Executives and engineers discussed a wide range of developmentsin, technical requirements of and outlook for active-matrix LCDsat a Semiconductor Equipment and Materials International tradegroup LCD manufacturing seminar in Kyoto, Japan.andP;  The market forthe LCDs is expected to rise from $700 million in 1991, of whichactive-matrix devices will constitute 16 percent, to $7 billion in1995 and $14 billion in the year 2000.andP;  Canon Inc expectslarge-scale production of 10-inch active-matrix color LCDs tostart in 1991 in order to achieve a price of $350 per display by1995.andP;  The demand for flat-panels in 1995 is expect to be about 17million units worth $6.8 billion, but that demand requires thatprices be in the $350 to $420 range.andP;  Some engineers havereservations as to whether the current large-size, active-matrixtechnology can be manufactured properly or reach the cost goals.andO;Design, engineering and manufacturing requirements and impacts ofever-larger active-matrix LCDs are discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Liquid Crystal DisplaysResearch and DevelopmentMarket AnalysisProduct DevelopmentSeminarsColorSizeRequirements AnalysisSystem DevelopmentSemiconductor Equipment and Materials InternationalManufacturingOutlook.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>